        "subject": "LU-10199 lfs: Fix file name comparison in lfs_migrate",
        "message": "LU-10199 lfs: Fix file name comparison in lfs_migrate\n\nThe sanity test 56xb revealed that the file name comparison between\nthe previously migrated files and the current file was incorrect.\nThis bug could cause a hard-linked file to get migrated more\nthan once.  The comparison now uses the absolute path to ensure\nthat an already migrated file is correctly detected.\n\nThe sanity test is reenabled now that the name comparison has\nbeen corrected.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial clientdistro=sles12sp3 testlist=sanity\nTest-Parameters: trivial clientdistro=el6.9 testlist=sanity\nSigned-off-by: Steve Guminski <stephenx.guminski@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I021c002dfd047bc9dcb35b19c1e5fd0b92bf69c3\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
